==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equipment
<hw>E*quip"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧quipement</ets>. See <er>Equip</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of equipping, or the state of being equipped, as for a
voyage or expedition.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>equipment</qex> of the fleet was hastened by De Witt.</q>
<rj><qau>Hume.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Whatever is used in equipping; necessaries for an
expedition or voyage; the collective designation for the articles
comprising an outfit; equipage; <as>as, a railroad <ex>equipment</ex>
(locomotives, cars, etc.</as> ; for carrying on business); horse
<xex>equipments</xex>; infantry <xex>equipments</xex>; naval
<xex>equipments</xex>; laboratory <xex>equipments</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Armed and dight,⟦br⟧
In the <qex>equipments</qex> of a knight.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equipoise</ent>⟦br⟧
